Construction of a Sh40 million Gender-Based Violence rescue centre is done.   The facility is one of the first national government's GBV rescue centres done courtesy of the National-Government Affirmative Action Fund.  It is at Nkomo Ward in Tigania West Sub-county and can house at least 1,000 persons.  Meru Women Representative Kawira Mwangaza said they would invite President Uhuru Kenyatta to open the centre once the final touches are done.   She regretted that the county suffered a significant number of gender-based violence cases.    Implement policies that protect women and girls, state urged  When missionaries gave up on the war against FGM  Government commits to ending gender violence in five years  Budget constraints hamper State's quest to fight gender-based violence  Dealing with cases of gender-based violence  Has the media objectively covered gender based violence? | The Newsroom  Chief arraigned in Maseno Court for defiling 14-year-old girl By Philip Muasya | 16 hours ago By Erastus Mulwa | 23 hours ago By Rose Mukonyo | 1 day ago By Steve Nzioka | 2 days ago